import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['size'] = pd.to_numeric(data['size'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='size', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['size'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of size in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['size'] = pd.to_numeric(data['size'], errors='coerce')
    avg_size = data.groupby('name')['size'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='name', y='size', data=avg_size)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('What is the average size of the items in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=avg_size['size'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average size')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['parent'] = data['parent'].astype('category')
    sns.boxplot(x='parent', y='size', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the size distribution of items by their parent?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['name', 'size']]
    sns.kdeplot(data=data, x='size', hue='name', fill=True, alpha=0.5, common_norm=False)
    plt.title('What is the size distribution of items by their name?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
